ext":"After two days was the feast of the passover, and of unleavened bread: and the chief priests and the scribes sought how they might take him by craft, and put him to death.","year":33},{"id":"recFmpvN0zVfEzHEa","ref":"Mark.14.2","text":"But they said, Not on the feast day, lest there be an uproar of the people.","year":33},{"id":"rechvgpuZNiGy65zK","ref":"Mark.14.3","text":"And being in Bethany in the house of Simon the leper, as he sat at meat, there came a woman having an alabaster box of ointment of spikenard very precious; and she brake the box, and poured it on his head.","year":33},{"id":"recqv66kSutjeZYbi","ref":"Mark.14.4","text":"And there were some that had indignation within themselves, and said, Why was this waste of the ointment made?","year":33},{"id":"rec7f3Yzfy4LgSRCZ","ref":"Mark.14.5","text":"For it might have been sold for more than three hundred pence, and have been given to the poor. And they murmured against her.","year":33},{"id":"recwzqG78iMrLB4Wd","ref":"Mark.14.6","text":"And Jesus said, Let her alone; why trouble ye her? she hath wrought a good work on me.","year":33},{"id":"reccDVJtBHFKBGCuk","ref":"Mark.14.7","text":"For ye have the poor with you always, and whensoever ye will ye may do them good: but me ye have not always.","year":33},{"id":"recwq74WwBzmWsFb8","ref":"Mark.14.8","text":"She hath done what she could: she is come aforehand to anoint my body to the burying.","year":33}]}
